column2: Three loon eggs on Department of Natural Resources raft.  2 loons in attendance-tame fox.
Two adult loons and one chick.
Sunny- wind 0-5 mph from SE. Lots of rain last week- 2+ inches. Osprey on lake last evening- kingfisher on lake today.
Partly cloudy- 77 degrees F.- W wind 5 mph. No significant rain for a week. Observed an immature eagle on log at lake's edge.
Mostly cloudy- wind negligible. Hard rain last night. 77 degrees F.- water 72 degrees F. Bloom of holopedium sp. cladophora present.
Sunny- wind 4-8 mph.- rain 2 nights ago. 72 degrees in the sun- water temp 67 degrees F.
Sunny- W wind 5-8 mph.- air temp 75 degrees. Surface water temp 70 degrees. Rain last night less than 1/2".
Clear and sunny- SE wind 3-6 mph.- air temp 53 degrees F.- surface water temp 50 degrees.  Male loon on lake last evening and this morning.
Ice went out yesterday in PM. A pair of loons on lake. Sighted several mallards. Cloudy. 5-8 mph wind SE. Hard rain yesterday. 43 deg F air. Surface water temp is 39 deg F.

Sunny- very windy. 15-25 mph SW wind. Water surface temp 52 deg F. Air temp 74 deg F. Pair of loons on lake almost every day. Put out loon nesting platform on lake yesterday. Eagles sighted twice last week.
Overcast with sun peeking out periodically. Windy. 20-30 mph SE wind. Surface water temp 54 deg F- air temp 62 deg F.
Sunny and overcast. Light wind out of west. 67 deg F air- Water surface temp is 57 deg F.
Sunny and windy. 15-25 mph SE wind. Water surface temp 59 deg F- Air temp 70 deg F.
Partly sunny. 65 deg F air. Water temp 60 deg F. E wind 5-10 mph. 1st sunny day in a week. Rained the last 7 days.
Overcast. Air temp is 48 deg F. Water surface temp is 53 deg F. N wind 5-10 mph. Rain and cold weather for last week. Frost on 5/29. Loon on nest.
Partly cloudy. Air = 78 deg F- water = 63 deg F. Loon on nest. 10-20 mph W wind.
Clear- sunny day. Winds 0-5 mph WSW. Water surface temp is 65 deg F. Air temp is 67 deg F. Loon egg hatched 6/17. Second egg abandoned and taken by predator. Mother loon and chick doing fine.
Partly cloudy- windy- 10-15 mph N wind. Air is 60 F- water is 69 F. Loons with chick.
Sunny. 5 mph N wind. Water temp 78 deg F. Air temp 81 deg F. Loon chick is diving. Observed a bald eagle and immature bald eagle.
Partly sunny. Light wind- SW at 5 mph. Air is 85 deg F- water = 80 deg F. 2" rain in last 2 days.
Sunny. Air temp is 87 F- water temp is 84 F. Calm. 1.5" rain last week.
Cloudy- air is 71 F- water is 76 F. 5-8 mph W wind. Cold front moved through 2 days ago. Night temps in upper 40's.
Sunny- clear. Air = 80 F- Water = 74 F. W wind at 5 mph. Daphnia bloom in deeper waters. ID'd as Holopedium sp. and Copepoda.
Sunny and windy. 5-15 mph NW wind. 72 deg F water temp. Air temp 77 deg F. Daphnia still present.
Sunny- no wind. Air 61 F- water 66 F. Had first frost 2 days ago. Loons have left. Flock of 12 common mergansers on lake this morning. 4" rain a week ago.
Overcast. No wind. Water temp 66 F. Air temp 64 F
Clear and sunny. Air is 60 deg F. Water surface temp is 60 deg F. 5-10 mph SW wind.
Partly sunny- windy day. NW wind 10-20 mph. Air temp 38 deg F. Water surface temp 56 deg F. First snow last night.
Sunny- air temp is 50 F- Water surface temp is 54 deg F. 5 mph SW wind.
Windy at 10-15 mph S- water temperature is 50 degrees- air temperature is 56 degrees- cloudy- and loons on lake.
Rainy- calm- water temperature is 48 degrees and air temperature is 42 degrees F.
Rainy- wind out of SW at 5 mph- air temperature is 57 degrees and water temperature is 55 degrees F.
Overcast- windy E at 10-15 mph- air temperature is 74 degrees and water temperature is 68 degrees F.
Windy- 10-15 mph NW wind- air temperature is 70 degrees and water temperature is 66 degrees F.
Dead calm- air temperature is 74 degrees- water temperature is 73 degrees- overcast and very humid.
Windy SW at 15-20 mph- water temperature is 80 degrees- sunny- air temperature is 90 degrees F- and very humid.
Breezy at 5-7 mph from south- air temperature is 81 degrees F- water temperature is 82 degrees F- partly sunny- and hazy.
Sunny- wind S at 5-8 mph- air temperature is 82 degrees and water temperature is 82 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- wind SW at 5-10 mph- water temperature is 81 degrees F- air temperature is 83 degrees F- and bad storm on 7/21.
Cloudy- wind W at 2-5 mph- air temperature is 73 degrees and water temperature is 77 degrees.
Sunny- windy SW at 8-10 mph- air temperature is 84 degrees and water temperature is 77 degrees.

Partly cloudy- wind 5-10 mph- water temp 63 F.
Sunny- air temp 74 F. Water temp 64 F. Wind NE 5-10 mph. Water level dropped 3" in last week.
Sunny- wind calm 0-5 mph- Water temp 64 F- air temp 68 F. Freezing temp last night 30 F.

Had a total of 8.6 inches of rain 72 hours previous to sampling. Water collected at the 40' depth had hydrogen sulfide odor.
Sunny and calm. Air temp. = 72F. Water is brown (tea color) after very heavy rains last November carried runoff from adjacent Taramack swamp into the lake. Water temp @ 3' =43.7F
Cloudy. Wind SE 5-8 mph. Water temp 52.8F
Partly cloudy. Wind Se 5-8 mph. Air temp. = 79F. Lots of pollen in lake. Windward shoreline was milkly-yellow. Water temp 68.3F- lots of pollen in lake.
Partly cloudy. Wind E 0-3 mph. Air Temp. = 77F. Some pollen still in lake.
Partly Sunny- Wind W- 5-8mph- .25" rain last night.
Sunny- wind W 0-3mph- temp last 2 nights- mid 40's
Partly Cloudy. Wind SW 8-12 mph. Partly Cloudy. Wind SW 8-12 mph. 2+ inches of rain in previous week.
Sunny- wind SE 3-5 mph- sporatic Daphnia in water.
